  "prompt": "If I delete my Tinder account and uninstall the app, does my profile still show to those I've matched with?",
  "response": "When you delete your Tinder account and uninstall the app, your profile is generally removed from the platform. Here's what typically happens:\n\n1. **Profile Visibility:**\n   - **To New Users:** Your profile will no longer appear to new potential matches. \n   - **To Existing Matches:** For users you've already matched with, your profile should disappear from their matches list. They may no longer be able to view your profile or communicate with you through the app.\n\n2. **Data Removal:**\n   - **Personal Information:** Deleting your account usually removes your personal information, photos, and chat history from Tinder's servers. However, some data might be retained in Tinder's backup systems for a certain period, as outlined in their [Privacy Policy](https://www.gotinder.com/privacy).\n\n3. **Reactivation:**\n   - If you decide to return to Tinder later, creating a new account typically means starting fresh, as your previous profile and matches won't be restored.\n\n4. **Uninstalling the App:**\n   - Uninstalling the Tinder app from your device doesn't delete your account. To fully remove your presence from Tinder, you must delete your account through the app or the Tinder website before uninstalling.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Paid Subscriptions:** If you have a Tinder Plus, Gold, or Platinum subscription, ensure that you've canceled it before deleting your account to avoid future charges.\n  \n- **Third-Party Sign-Ins:** If you signed up for Tinder using Facebook or another third-party service, you might need to adjust your account settings there as well to fully disconnect your profile.\n\n- **Support Contact:** If you encounter issues or if your profile remains visible after deletion, it's advisable to contact Tinder's customer support for assistance.\n\n**Final Note:**\nWhile deleting your account typically removes your visibility on the platform, it's always a good idea to review Tinder's latest [Help Center](https://www.help.tinder.com/) or [Privacy Policy](https://www.gotinder.com/privacy) for the most current information, as app functionalities and policies can change over time.",
